# All Rust sources are LF. Without this, a Windows checkout under
# `core.autocrlf=true` rewrites whole files to CRLF on commit — polluting
# diffs + blame with thousands of phantom line changes. That is exactly how
# CRLF slipped into three `raft` sources via PR #178. Enforcing eol=lf here
# makes it impossible regardless of a contributor's local git config.
*.rs text eol=lf
